---
interface Props {
  locale?: "en" | "th";
}

const { locale = "en" } = Astro.props;

const copy = {
  en: {
    eyebrow: "site guide",
    title: "How to use Electrical Atlas",
    subtitle:
      "Think of this prototype as a learning map, not a finished textbook. Start with one guided lesson, then use the subject map to see where every future topic will live.",
    quickStartTitle: "Quick start",
    quickStartIntro: "If you are not sure what to click, use this order:",
    quickStart: [
      {
        title: "1. Read the guide first",
        body: "You are here. This page explains what each part of the prototype is for.",
        href: "/en/guide/",
        label: "Stay here",
      },
      {
        title: "2. Start the first lesson",
        body: "Use “What Is Electricity?” to learn the site’s teaching style: visual explanation first, technical detail when needed.",
        href: "/en/lessons/what-is-electricity/",
        label: "Open first lesson",
      },
      {
        title: "3. Open the knowledge map",
        body: "Use the map when you want to browse by subject, component, system, application, or prerequisite path.",
        href: "/en/map/",
        label: "Open map",
      },
    ],
    currentPartsTitle: "What exists right now",
    currentParts: [
      {
        name: "Home",
        body: "A landing page that shows the project direction and the main entry points.",
      },
      {
        name: "First lesson",
        body: "A finished prototype lesson about charge, fields, voltage, current, and a battery lighting a lamp.",
      },
      {
        name: "MOSFET lesson",
        body: "The first full component lesson. It explains structure, gate field control, switching behavior, gate charge, and application areas.",
      },
      {
        name: "Subject map",
        body: "The big atlas index. It currently exposes 1,607 mapped topics from the Markdown knowledge inventory.",
      },
      {
        name: "Search",
        body: "A way to find where a topic belongs and open its mapped topic record. Topic records are not full lessons yet.",
      },
      {
        name: "Language switch",
        body: "The globe button shows the current language. Click it to go to the same page in the other language when that page exists.",
      },
      {
        name: "Suggested next",
        body: "The end of each lesson or topic record points to related lessons, nearby topics, prerequisites, or practical applications.",
      },
    ],
    lessonTitle: "How to read a lesson",
    lessonSteps: [
      "Start in Guided mode if the topic is new.",
      "Use Technical mode when you want equations, precise terms, or engineering vocabulary.",
      "Treat interactive diagrams as concept builders. They are not circuit simulators yet.",
      "Use safety notes seriously. The site is for learning; live wiring and standards work need verified sources and qualified practice.",
    ],
    mapTitle: "How to use the subject map",
    mapSteps: [
      "Browse the subject backbone to understand the big structure.",
      "Use search for a specific word like MOSFET, battery, Coulomb, transformer, or IEC.",
      "Open a topic record to learn its primary home, type, domain, and summary.",
      "If the record exists but no lesson exists yet, that means the topic is mapped but not published.",
    ],
    statusTitle: "Important status rule",
    statusBody:
      "Mapped does not mean published. The atlas can know where MOSFET gate charge belongs before the MOSFET lesson is fully written, illustrated, reviewed, translated, and tested.",
    pathsTitle: "Choose your path",
    paths: [
      {
        label: "I am a beginner",
        route: "Guide → First lesson → Subject map → Search simple parts",
      },
      {
        label: "I want a component",
        route: "Subject map → Search component name → Open topic record → Ask for that lesson next",
      },
      {
        label: "I want Thai engineering context",
        route: "Thai pages → Safety/standards topics → verified TISI, EIT, MEA, PEA, ERC, NBTC, NIMT references later",
      },
    ],
    nextTitle: "What I recommend next",
    nextBody:
      "Now that the MOSFET component lesson exists, the next build step should be topic-to-lesson relationships: prerequisites, successor topics, and related component/circuit links.",
  },
  th: {
    eyebrow: "คู่มือใช้งานเว็บ",
    title: "วิธีใช้ Electrical Atlas",
    subtitle:
